The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the National 9/11 Pentagon Memorial in Washington, D.C. on September 11, 2018. Pence paid tribute to the victims of the 9/11 attacks and expressed gratitude to those who have worked to rebuild and protect the nation. He highlighted the heroism and resilience displayed by Americans on that day and emphasized the importance of remembering and learning from the events of 9/11. Pence also praised the men and women serving in the Armed Forces and highlighted the administration's efforts to strengthen the military. He concluded his remarks by honoring the fallen and offering a prayer for their families and those who continue to fight for freedom.